**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE INSTRUCTIONS: change instructions here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
<instruct>
/ wait = 1000 
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3.0%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ navigationbuttonfontstyle = ("Arial", 3.0%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ screencolor = black
/ txcolor = white
</instruct>


<page begin1>
<br><br><center><big><b>Thank you for your interest in the <i>Alcohol Go/No-go Association Task</i>.</b></big><br><br><br>
<i>Please read the instructions carefully before proceeding with the task.</i></center><br><br>
This work assumes that you can read English fluently, and that your vision is normal or corrected 
to normal.<br><br> 
The tasks that you will be doing in this experiment involve category judgment. For 
instance, in one condition your task may be to search for all the words that represent the 
categories '<%item.attributeAlabel.item(1)%>.' (e.g., <%item.attributea.item(1)%>, <%item.attributea.item(2)%>) 
or the category '<%item.targetalabel.item(1)%>' (e.g., <%item.targeta.item(1)%>, <%item.targeta.item(2)%>).<br><br>
All categorizations will be made with the SPACEBAR <%expressions.buttoninstruct1%>.  When you see a word that 
belongs to either one of the two categories (e.g., '<%item.attributeAlabel.items.1%>' or '<%item.targetAlabel.items.1%>') hit the spacebar <%expressions.buttoninstruct1%> as fast 
as possible. Ignore words that do not belong to either category. 
</page>

<page begin2>
<br><br>The words you will be looking for will be from the 3 groups listed below. Some examples are provided for each category:<br><br>
<%item.targetAlabel.item(1)%></font> (white letters): <%item.targetA.item(1)%>,<%item.targetA.item(2)%>, <%item.targetA.item(3)%>, 
<%item.targetA.item(4)%>, <%item.targetA.item(5)%>, ...<br><br>
<font color='turquoise'><%item.attributeAlabel.item(1)%> (blue letters): <%item.attributeA.item(1)%>,<%item.attributeA.item(2)%>, <%item.attributeA.item(3)%>, 
<%item.attributeA.item(4)%>, <%item.attributeA.item(5)%>, ...<br><br>
<%item.attributeBlabel.item(1)%> (blue letters): <%item.attributeB.item(1)%>,<%item.attributeB.item(2)%>, 
<%item.attributeB.item(3)%>, <%item.attributeB.item(4)%>, <%item.attributeB.item(5)%>, ...</font><br><br><br>
All '<%item.attributeAlabel.item(1)%>' and '<%item.attributeBlabel.item(1)%>' items are descriptive (adjectives or adverbs), while 
'<%item.targetAlabel.item(1)%>' are all objects (nouns).  The color coding of the words is there to help distinguish between 
the <font color='turquoise'><b>evaluative (<%item.attributeAlabel.item(1)%> and <%item.attributeBlabel.item(1)%>) words</b></font>
and the <b>object categories</b>.
</page>

<page begin3>
<br><br>
The task will <u>get faster and harder</u> as you get further along. In fact, you may at 
times find it very difficult to correctly classify ANY of the trials. Do not despair.  
This task is designed to be difficult and no one is expected to perform it perfectly.  
Please persevere and just try to catch as many words as possible.<br><br>
You will have an opportunity to practice each new set before the task begins.^^
Hit the spacebar <%expressions.buttoninstruct1%> when you are ready to begin.
</page>

<page end>
<center><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>
You have reached the end of the task.
<h1>Thank you!</h1></center>
</page>

<item reminders>
/ 1 = "Words will appear in the center of the screen, one by one, at high speed. These words may or may not belong to the category you see printed at the top.
~nPress the space bar as fast as you can if the word belongs to the category you see at the top. If they do not belong to the category, don't do anything. Just wait for the next word.
~nIf you made an error, a red X appears below the word. Otherwise, you will see a green 'O'.
~n~n~nPress the space bar to start."
/ 2 = "New category!
~nPress the space bar to start the categorization trials for this new category."
/ 3 = "The set-up has changed. Instead of only one category, you now see TWO categories printed at the top.
~nPress the space bar as fast as you can if the word appearing in the center belongs to EITHER one of the two categories you see at the top. Don't do anything if the word does not belong to either one of the categories.
~n~n~nPress the space bar to practice these two categories."
/ 4 = "New categories! 
~nPress the space bar to practice the new categories"
</item>

<text testTrialStart>
/ items = ("You are now starting the main trials for the same two categories.
~nPress the space bar as fast as you can if the word appearing in the center belongs to EITHER one of the two categories you see at the top.
~n~n~nPress the space bar to start.")
/ position = (50%, 65%) 
/ size = (60%, 50%)
/ txcolor = white 
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 2.67%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ vjustify = center
/ hjustify = center
</text>

<text speedup>
/ items = ("The next set of blocks is faster than the last.  Get ready!")
/ position = (50, 75) 
/ txcolor = white 
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 2.67%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
</text>

<expressions>
/ buttoninstruct1 = if (computer.touch && !computer.hasKeyboard) {"button";} else {"key";}
/ buttoninstruct2 = if (computer.touch && !computer.hasKeyboard) {"using response buttons on your screen"} else {"on the keyboard";}
</expressions>

